The paper focuses on the problem of differentially private histogram publication, which is related to data management and privacy (cs.DB). The paper also discusses differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a modular approach to designing differentially private histogram publication schemes, which involves combining simple modules to create more complex schemes. This approach involves optimization and algorithm design, which are topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing and evaluating the performance of different schemes, which involves statistical analysis and experimental evaluation (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses information theory and the concept of mutual information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
